Texas A&M University K500 superconducting cyclotron
spectrometer was used to separate the reaction
loss was measured in the ionization chamber. The
position of the particles along the dispersive x
direction was measured with resistive wires at four
different depths within the detector, separated by
NE102A plastic scintillator located in air
behind the exit window of the detector measured
The whole detector setup i.e. magnetic spectrometer
with focal plane detector are able to identify nuclei
